titleStmt.title: A letter from the Kings Majesties court at Hampton; concerning the Commissioners of the Lords and Commons of the Parliament of Eugland [sic], and the Commissioners of the Estates of Scotlands delivering of the propositions to the King, upon Tuesday last at Hampton-Court. And the proceedings of the Kings Majesty thereupon. Also, a message to the Estates of Scotland, and the coming into England of the Lord Lanerick, with the treatie and Covenant, to present to His Gracious Majesty.
